field.label: Creator(s)
field.hint: Enter the name(s) of the creator(s) of this resource.
field.required: You must enter the creator of the resource

field.label: Title
field.hint: Enter the main title of the resource.
field.required: You must enter a main title for this resource.

field.label: Publication Date
field.hint: Please give the date of previous publication or public distribution. You can leave out the day and/or month if they aren't applicable.

field.label: Publisher
field.hint: Enter the name of the publisher of the previously issued instance of this resource.

field.label: Language
field.hint: Select the language(s) of the files associated with this resource. If you select more than one language, you may also wish to indicate or explain this under 'Description'.

field.label: Resource Type
field.hint: Select the resource type(s) of the main content of the resource (hold Ctrl/Cmd while clicking to select multiple resource types).
field.required: You must choose one or multiple resource types

field.label: Subject
field.hint: Please select a subject tag that describes the primary topic for this resource.

field.label: Subject (Other)
field.hint: Please enter a custom subject tag.

field.label: Prerequisite Knowledge
field.hint: Please list one prerequisite at a time (press the "Add More" button to add more entries). Some examples of prerequisites are "familiarity with interpreting histograms" and "central limit theorem".

field.label: Learning Objectives
field.hint: Please list one objective at a time (press the "Add More" button to add more entries).
field.required: Please enter learning objectives for this resource.

field.label: Description
field.hint: Describe this resource in detail: Overarching aims for the resource; Expand on the learning outcomes and topics addressed; Mention data sets used or studies referred to; whether the resource forms part of a larger set of related resources.

field.label: Summary
field.hint: Please provide a one line summary of the above description that would be most useful for someone browsing your resource. This is used as the short blurb shown in search results. E.g.: "This web visualization demonstrates the concept of a sampling distribution of an estimate, using the example of a mean of a Normally distributed variable."

field.label: Related Resources
field.hint:
Please list one related resource at a time (press the "Add Resource" button to add more entries).

My Submissions: this will create a link to an approved resource that you previously submitted to StatSpace. One use of this feature is to link a series of resources, each dealing with a different topic (chapters in a book, lecture slides, or tutorials); you may want to link this resource to the next resource in the series. You may also wish to link to versions of your resource that are available in other languages. Link(s) will appear at the bottom of the generated resource page. For more information, please hover your mouse over the information icon.

Other Related Resources: this will create a link to an external resource, or to a StatSpace resource submitted by another contributor. This link will appear in the side bar.

field.label: Suggested Uses, Tips and Discoveries
field.hint: Include information that will help others to use this material. Also include lessons you've learned from using this material in practice, e.g.: what worked, what didn't, or what was particularly difficult.

field.label: Access
field.hint: You may make this entire submission accessible only to instructors; only instructors will know that this submission exists. Alternatively, if you choose to let everyone access this submission, in the Upload step you may configure individual files to be accessible only to instructors.
field.required: You must choose an access level.

field.label: Creation Date
field.hint: If you know when this resource was created, please give the date. You can leave out the day and/or month if they aren't applicable.
